 works in Milan, Italy\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>SOLO EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi / Alberta Pellacani, Spazio Aperto, GAM  Galleria dArte Moderna diBologna, Bologna, Italy, December 19, 1997  January 7, 1998, curated by Walter Guadagniniand Dede Auregli.\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi: Foolish Things, Eldorado project room, GAMeC  Galleria dArteModerna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, February 9  March 30, 2003, curated byGiacinto Di Pietrantonio and Alessandro Rabottini.\r\nRoberto Cuoghi, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 29  October 30,2003.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nThe Wrong Gallery, New York, USA, March 730, 2005, curated by Maurizio Cattelan,Massimiliano Gioni, and Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>\r\nMei Gui, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 22  October 4, 2006.\r\nMbube, objectif_exhibitions, Antwerp, Belgium, October 26  November 25, 2006, curatedby Tommy Simoens. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi: Mei Gui, Centre International dArt et du Paysage de lle de Vassivire,Beaumont du Lac, France, January 17, 2007. Presented in the context of Un million etquarante-quatrime anniversaire de lart / 1 000 044 candles for art, held on January 17 invarious venues throughout France.\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\nuillakku, Castello di Rivoli Museo dArte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, May 6 July 27, 2008, curated by M. Beccaria. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to ICA  Institute of Contemporary Arts, London, UK, October 14  November23, 2008.]\r\n\r\n<strong>2011</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi, UCLA Hammer Museum, Los Angeles, USA, January 22  May 15, 2011,curated by Ali Subotnick. Brochure.\r\n\r\n<strong>2012</strong>\r\nZOLOTO, Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, May 30  July 13, 2012.\r\n\r\n<strong>2014</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi: uillakku Corral, New Museum, New York, USA, April 30  June 29, 2014,curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Margot Norton. Catalogue.\r\nDa i e pigal a i e i o pigal e pigal, Le Consortium, centre dart, Dijon, France,October 17, 2014  January 11, 2015. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, February 13  May 31, 2015]\r\n\r\n<strong>2016</strong>\r\nPutiferio, DESTE Foundation Project Space, Slaughterhouse, Hydra, Greece, June 21 September 30, 2016.\r\n\r\n<strong>2017</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi: Perla Pollina, 19962016, Centre dArt Contemporain Genve, Geneva,Switzerland, February 22  April 30, 2017, curated by Andrea Bellini. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveling to Madre  Museo darte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, May 15 \r\nSeptember 11, 2017]\r\nImitazione di Cristo; Il Mondo Magico (The Magical World), Italian Pavilion, 57 Biennaledi Venezia, Venice, Italy, May 13  November 26, curated by Cecilia Alemani. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>GROUP EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>1996</strong>\r\nOrizzontale verticale: Giovani artisti modenesi, 1a edizione, Palazzo della Provincia, Modena,Italy, December 14, 1996  January 25, 1997, curated by Roberto Daolio and Corrado Levi.Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\nMenotrenta: 2a selezione di giovani artisti, Spazio Laboratorio Hajech, Milan, Italy, February 11 March 8, 1997, curated by Francesca Pensa and Francesco Tedeschi. Catalogue.\r\nLAB.12.2 - T.I.N.A. (there is no alternative), Viafarini, Milan, Italy, April 18  May 2, 1997,curated by R. Daolio.\r\nConversazione in giardino, Orto Botanico, Ferrara, Italy, September 27  October 19, 1997, curatedby Gilberto Pellizzola. Catalogue.\r\nRaccolta del disegno contemporaneo: Nuove acquisizioni 19941997, Palazzina dei Giardini,Modena, Italy, November 30, 1997  January 25, 1998, curated by Claudia Zanfi. Brochure.\r\nVisual Rave, La Societ Umanitaria, Milan, Italy, December 12, 1997  January 12, 1998, curatedby Antonio dAvossa and Centro Arte a Parte. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>1999</strong>\r\nFine, Studio Armin Linke, Milan, Italy, May 31  June 18, 1999, curated by Lorenzo Silvan.Catalogue.\r\nGuarene Arte 99, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo per lArte, September 25  November 7,1999, Guarene dAlba (Cuneo), Italy, selected by Emanuela De Cecco. Catalogue.\r\nIn Camera Caritatis, Globale Positionen 10, Museum in Progress, Vienna, Austria, curated byMassimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<strong>2000</strong>\r\n3nds: Milano, Salara, Bologna, Italy, May 19  June 13, 2000, curated by Alessandra Galasso andGianfranco Maraniello. Catalogue.\r\nFuori Uso 2000. The Bridges: Art on the highway / Arte in autostrada, Lungo fiume sud, Pescara,Italy, July 219, 2000, curated by Helena Kontova, Emanuela De Cecco, Hou Hanru, and AndreasSchlaegel &amp; Angela Rosenberg. Catalogue.\r\nFai da te / The Amateur View, Sparwasser HQ, Berlin, Germany, December 8, 2000  January,2001, curated by Luca Cerizza.\r\n\r\n<strong>2001</strong>\r\nPrimo piano: Su la testa! Opere e argomenti in scena, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro ArteContemporanea, Siena, Italy, February 411, 2001, curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\nMagic and Loss in Pandmonium: Biennial of Moving Images 2001, The Lux Centre, London, UK,March 2  April 8, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\r\n[The exhibition was also presented at Artistinvetrina, Fendissime, Rome, Italy, March 26, 2001, incollaboration with The British School at Rome; CAC Contemporary Art Centre, Vilnius, Lithuania,March 21  April 15, 2001: Magic &amp; Loss: Video by young Italian artists, MAN  Museo dArteProvincia di Nuoro, Nuoro, Italy, April 6  May 6, 2001: Magic and Loss: Contemporary ItalianVideo.]\r\nPlay &gt;, Openspace, Milan, Italy, March 28  April 29, 2001, curated by Gigiotto del Vecchio.Catalogue.\r\nEspresso: Arte oggi in Italia, Manifattura Tabacchi, Florence, Italy, June 10  July 20, 2001,curated by Luca Cerizza and Gianfranco Maraniello. The exhibition was part of Boom!, a programof five exhibitions curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\nIl dono: Offerta, ospitalit, insidia / The Gift: Generous Offerings, Threatening Hospitality, Palazzodelle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, June 2  September 23, 2001, curated byGianfranco Maraniello, Sergio Risaliti, and Antonio Somaini, organized by ICI  IndependentCurators International. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to Centro Culturale Candiani, Mestre (Venice), Italy, October 14, 2001  January 6,2002; Scottsdale Museum of Contemporary Art, Scottsdale, USA, February 7  May 5, 2002;Bronx Museum of the Arts, Bronx, USA, November 27, 2002  March 2, 2003; Mary and LeighBlock Museum of Art, Northwestern University, Evanston, USA, April 4  June 22, 2003; ArtGallery of Hamilton, Hamilton, Canada, August 9  October 18, 2003.]\r\nVideorom in The 1st Valencia Biennial: Communication between the Arts, various venues,Valencia, Spain, June 13  October 20, 2001, curated by Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\r\nThe End of All Things, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from June 20, 2001.\r\nTirana Biennale 1: Escape, National Gallery and Chinese Pavilion, Tirana, Albania, September 15 October 15, 2001, invited by Jens Hoffmann. Catalogue.\r\nIn fumo: Arte, fumetto, comunicazione / In fumo: Art, comics, communication, GAMeC  Galleria\r\ndArte Moderna e Contemporanea di Bergamo, Bergamo, Italy, September 27, 2001  January 6,\r\n2002, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2002</strong>\r\nManifesta 4: European Biennial of Contemporary Art, various venues, Frankfurt, Germany, May 25 August 25, 2002, curated by Iara Boubnova, Nuria Enguita Mayo, and Stphanie MoisdonTrembley. Catalogue.\r\nVerso il futuro: Identit nellarte italiana 19902002, Museo del Corso, Rome, Italy, June 26 August 25, 2002, curated by Costantino DOrazio and Ludovico Pratesi. Catalogue.\r\nExIt: Nuove geografie della creativit italiana, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy,September 21, 2002  January 6, 2003, curated by Francesco Bonami.\r\nPolyphonix 40, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, October 110, 2002, curated by ManuelaCorti. Catalogue.\r\nVideoROM 4.0, ex Mattatoio Testaccio, Rome, Italy, October 11, 2002, curated by CristianaPerrella.\r\nNuovo spazio italiano / New Italian Space, Galleria Civica di Arte Contemporanea, Trento andPalazzo delle Albere  MART Museo dArte Moderna e Contemporanea di Trento e Rovereto,Trento, Italy, December 7, 2002  February 23, 2003, curated by Fabio Cavallucci, GiovannaNicoletti, and Giorgio Verzotti. Catalogue.\r\nIronie, territorialit, stupeur, Teatro al Parco, Parma, Italy, December 17, 2002.Video program curated by Manuela Corti, in the context of Stanze aperte: Parma Poesia OpenFestival, curated by Daniela Rossi, Parma, December 1722, 2002.\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\nSpcial Ddicace, Muse dpartemental dart contemporain de Rochechouart, Rochechouart,France, March 21  August, 31, 2003, curated by Sadane Afif and Mathieu Mercier.\r\nHaluk Akakce, Roberto Cuoghi, Anna Gaskell, Christian Holstad, Raymond Pettibon, DavidShrigley, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from April 16, 2003.\r\nCover Theory: Larte contemporanea come re-interpretazione, Officina della luce, ex CentraleEmilia, Piacenza, Italy, May 11  June 29, 2003, curated by Marco Senaldi. Catalogue.\r\nCos va il mondo, Fondation dEntreprise Ricard, Paris, France, June 327, 2003, curated byCharlotte Laubard.\r\n2003 Summer Program, Apexart, New York, USA, June 25  July 26, 2003, organized by KatySiegel with Michele Maccarone and Mitchell Algus. Brochure.\r\nCynical Culture, Galerie Schppenhauer, Cologne, Germany, November 7  December 20, 2003,curated by Steven Rand.\r\nFuori Uso 2003: Great Expectations!, Ferrotel, Pescara, Italy, November 29, 2003  January 9,2004, curated by Charlotte Laubard, Chiara Parisi, Alessandro Rabottini, and Marcello Smarrelli.Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2004</strong>\r\nPerspectif cinema 20032004, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, January 29, 2004. Videoprogram.\r\nI Nuovi Mostri, a poster project by Fondazione Nicola Trussardi, Milan, Italy, February  March,2004, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to Venice, September 2004.]\r\nParadiso e Inferno, Fondazione Bevilacqua La Masa, Venice, Italy, May 7  August 23, 2004,curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio. Catalogue.\r\nVernice: Sentieri della giovane pittura italiana / Vernice: Pathways Through Young ItalianPainting, Villa Manin Centro dArte Contemporanea, Passariano (Udine), Italy, May 30 November 7, 2004, curated by Francesco Bonami and Sarah Cosulich Canarutto. Catalogue.\r\nMediterraneans: Arte Contemporanea, MACRO al Mattatoio, Rome, Italy, June 3  September 19,2004.\r\nAfter School Special, Ex scuole comunali, Locarno, Switzerland, August 314, 2004, curated byCristina Del Ponte, Riccardo Lisi, and Noah Stolz.\r\nDimensione follia: Soggettivit, passione ed eccesso nella quotidianit, Galleria Civica di ArteContemporanea, Trento, Italy, September 24, 2004  January 9, 2005, curated by Roberto Pinto.\r\nXI Esposizione nazionale darte: Artisti per Epicentro, Museo Epicentro  Arte contemporanea sumattonelle, Barcellona Pozzo di Gotto (Messina), Italy, December 1231, 2004, curated by NinoAbbate. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nFuori tema, Italian Feeling, XIV Quadriennale darte, Galleria Nazionale dArte Moderna, Rome,Italy, March 9  May 31, 2005. Catalogue.\r\nI Still Believe in Miracles: Dessins sans papier, ARC  Muse dArt Moderne de la Ville de Paris,Paris, France, April 7  May 7, 2005, curated by Laurence Boss, Anne Dressen, Hans UlrichObrist, and Angeline Scherf. Catalogue.\r\nStrata: Difference and Repetition, Fondazione Davide Halevim, Milan, Italy, May 27  July 2,2005, curated by Edoardo Gnemmi.\r\nChanges of Mind: Belief and Transformation, Haunch of Venison, London, UK, July 7  August25, 2005. Catalogue.\r\nVideominuto Pop TV, Centro per lArte Contemporanea Luigi Pecci, Prato, PAN Palazzo delle Artidi Napoli, Naples, and Enzimi: Festival della creativit contemporanea, Castel Porziano beach(Rome), Italy, September, 810, 2005.\r\nThe IX Baltic Triennia